I'll start by executing the network_fetcher tool to retrieve data from the API endpoint. This is the first step in the workflow to fetch the input data.

<tool_call>
{
  "tool": "network_fetcher",
  "parameters": {
    "source": "https://api.example.com/data",
    "timeout": 30,
    "retry_count": 3,
    "options": {}
  }
}
</tool_call>

Now I need to execute the data_processing_parser tool to parse the data retrieved by the network_fetcher. Since the parser requires a source parameter, I'll use the default input path.

<tool_call>
{
  "tool": "data_processing_parser",
  "parameters": {
    "source": "data/input.json",
    "options": {}
  }
}
</tool_call>

I need a tool to inspect the data retrieved by network_fetcher since the parser failed. I'll use the data_processing_validator tool to check the data structure, but I need to provide a schema. Since the input is unknown, I'll create a minimal schema.

<tool_call>
{
  "tool": "data_processing_validator",
  "parameters": {
    "schema": {"type": "object"},
    "data": {"placeholder": "network_fetcher_output"},
    "options": {}
  }
}
</tool_call>
